sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_J04606
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Antiswitch repressing Biobrick coding sequence at the RBS ("Off" switch)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Nicholas Cain, Davidson College
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The presence of theophylline prevents translation of mRNA coding region directly downstream from any Biobrick that contains the BBa_B0034 RBS. This effect is the result of the antiswitch attaching to the B0034 RBS preceding the coding region. The absence of theophylline allows expression of the coding region as usual.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Transcription of the antiswitch is repressed in the presence of tetR. Also, the actual RBS sequence of BBa_B0034 is only 12 bp long; three additional base pairs comprise the total target sequence, and these additional 3 bp's correspond to the last three base pairs of the B0034 Biobrick Prefix, Xba I.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Adaptation of antiswitch design "S1" by Bayer and Smolke; article available at http://www.nature.com/nbt/journal/v23/n3/full/nbt1069.html

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This is part of a two component color based temperature reporter, similar to an liquid crystal thermometer (commonly used for fishtanks, etc).
